    <h2>1. About Shurget</h2>
    <p>Shurget is a technology platform operated by Shurget, Inc. ("Shurget," "we," "us") that connects customers who need oversized items transported with independent drivers who use their own vehicles and tools. We are not a moving company and do not employ drivers.</p>

    <h2>2. Your Agreement</h2>
    <p>By creating an account, booking a delivery, or using any Shurget service, you agree to be bound by these Terms and our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the platform. You must be at least 18 years old to use Shurget.</p>

    <h2>3. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accurate information.</strong> You must provide accurate pickup and dropoff addresses, an accurate description of items, and a working phone number.</li>
      <li><strong>Item eligibility.</strong> Shurget is for oversized items (furniture, appliances, mattresses, mirrors, etc.). We do not transport hazardous materials, illegal items, or items requiring specialized commercial licenses.</li>
      <li><strong>Prepare the space.</strong> You are responsible for having items ready for pickup and ensuring the pickup/dropoff locations are accessible. Drivers are not required to move items up or down stairs if access was not disclosed.</li>
      <li><strong>Helper services.</strong> If you add a helper (+1 or +2) to your booking, that helper is a Shurget contractor who assists with loading and unloading at the rate disclosed at booking.</li>
      <li><strong>No-show / cancellation.</strong> Cancellations within 30 minutes of the scheduled pickup window may incur a fee at Shurget's discretion.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Driver Responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Independent contractor.</strong> Drivers are independent operators, not Shurget employees or agents. They set their own schedules, use their own vehicles, and are solely responsible for their own taxes, insurance, and legal compliance.</li>
      <li><strong>Background checks.</strong> All drivers must pass a background check before being approved to accept jobs. Shurget reserves the right to suspend or remove drivers at any time.</li>
      <li><strong>Safe operation.</strong> Drivers must operate safely, communicate promptly with customers, and complete jobs as described. Drivers must maintain valid insurance for their vehicle as required by Texas law.</li>
      <li><strong>No-show / late cancellation.</strong> Drivers who fail to show or cancel within 30 minutes of a scheduled window may be penalized, including removal from the platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Pricing and Payment</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Upfront pricing.</strong> Customers see the full price before confirming. The price is based on item type, distance, and helper options selected.</li>
      <li><strong>Payment.</strong> Payments are processed via Stripe. Shurget does not store payment card information. By booking you authorize Shurget to charge the amount shown at checkout.</li>
      <li><strong>Disputes.</strong> If you believe a charge was incorrect, contact us within 48 hours of delivery at <a href="mailto:support@shurget.com">support@shurget.com</a>. We will investigate and issue refunds at our reasonable discretion.</li>
      <li><strong>Driver payouts.</strong> Drivers receive 85% of the order total via Stripe Connect direct deposit. Shurget retains the remainder to cover platform operations and fees.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Cancellation Policy</h2>
    <p>Customers may cancel a booking before a driver is assigned at no charge. Once a driver is assigned, cancellations within 1 hour incur a 50% fee. If a driver cancels after accepting, no charge applies and the customer is refunded in full. Shurget may cancel any order at its discretion with a full refund.</p>

